## 1. Headline finding

`E_log2_base_operand` — the substrate observable already validated as the 1D C-extractor in MCG Phase 2g — is **K_G's substrate-derived cousin within each varying-K_G fixture**.

| Fixture | Spearman ρ(E, K_G) | Classification | n_rows |
|---|---|---|---|
| Schwarzschild | **−1.0000** | monotone_decreasing | 137 |
| pure_algebraic | **−1.0000** | monotone_decreasing | 137 |
| SR (control, constant K_G) | +0.0042 (noise) | non_monotone | 137 |

Perfect rank-monotone relationship across the entire 137-row sweep in both fixtures. K_G goes up → E goes down, every step.

The relationship is **fixture-bound**: at matched K_G across Schwarzschild and pure_algebraic, E values do not agree (5/5 sampled pairs mismatch within 0.5 log2 units). The substrate encoding is fixture-specific.

